Get an array of powers of a number 2: [1, 2, 4, 8, 16 ... ]
Write a function named power of Two that takes the number n as an argument and returns an array of powers of 2 (powers from 0 to n).
Example:

the power of Two(2) function should return [1, 2, 4];
the power of Two(4) function should return [1, 2, 4, 8, 16] .
function powersOfTwo(n){
  let arr=[];
   while ( n >= 0) { 
    arr.unshift(Math.pow(2, n));
    n--;
  }
 return arr;
}
